# Revit API (C#) — Core Rules

## Non-negotiables

- All Revit API calls must run on Revit main thread.
- Modeless WPF must use `ExternalEvent` + `IExternalEventHandler` for any Revit action.
- Keep transaction scope minimal; never hold `Transaction` during long operations.

## Performance

- Filter early with `FilteredElementCollector`: `OfClass`/`OfCategory`/`WherePasses`.
- Avoid `ToElements()` too early; avoid multiple enumerations.
- Store `ElementId` (not long-lived `Element` references) when passing around.

## Reliability

- Guard `uiapp`/`uidoc`/`doc`/`selection` before use.
- User cancel → `Result.Cancelled` (not `Failed`).
- Exception messages must include: feature/command name + context + sample element ids.

## No Invention

- Do not invent patterns: always scan repo first (namespaces, base classes, logging, DI).
